The teaching method will be a mix of lecture and discussion.

Later sessions will require students to undertake some guided/independent research and group work about recent failures of corporate governance and reform efforts, including a final written assignment.

The objective of the course is to give students a basis for evaluating public policy related to corporate governance and assessing corporate performance, whether as a regulator, a member of a corporation (officer, director or employee) or an investor/stockholder.

