第1回 Introduction
What is a corporation? A brief history of the corporate form and presentation of key attributes of the corporation -- limited liability, perpetual existence, transferable ownership and centralized management. 
第2回 Introduction -- continued
Basic structure of the corporation. Shareholders, directors, officers and employees; role of creditors. The corporate charter and “ultra vires” actions.

第3回 Director roles
Duties of directors. Agent-principal relationships. Duty of care - introduction.

第4回 Duty of care -- business judgment.
Duty of care. The business judgment rule. The doctrine of corporate waste. 
第5回 Duty of Loyalty
The duty of loyalty -- Conflicts of interest. The doctrine of corporate opportunities.

第6回 Control Mechanisms - 1
Shareholder voting. Voting requirements, bylaws/rules, proxy rules

第7回 Control Mechanisms - 2
Shareholder derivative litigation.

第8回 Control Mechanisms - 3
M&A and the market for corporate control. Court-imposed limits upon takeover defenses in the U.S. and Japan.

第9回 Control Mechanisms - 4
Securities regulatory and stock exchange disclosure and governance requirements.

第10回 Governance Failures 1 -- The 1999 U.S. technology and telecom bubble
The Enron and Worldcom accounting scandals and other related governance failures.

第11回 Governance Failures 2 -- the response
A look at corporate governance reforms in response to the 1999-2000 technology/telecom bubble. The Sarbanes-Oxley Act and related efforts.

第12回 Governance Failures 2 -- The Housing Bubble and 2008 financial crisis
Governance failures in financial institutions and their role in the 2008 global financial crisis.

第13回 Governance Failures 2 -- the response
A look at responses to the governance failures identified as causes of the 2008 financial crisis, including some key provisions of the Dodd-Frank Act and the "Volcker Role"

第14回 Corporate Governance Issues in Japan
A look at some of the major corporate governance issues in Japan -- the role of cross-shareholdings; lack of outside directors; limited shareholder influence; the role of Japanese culture as a controlling influence.

その他
The final assignment will be written work on a current corporate governance topic related to one of the class sessions.

